abstract: McDonald's reports third-quarter profit of $1.51 billion, or $1.45 per share, up 9 percent from year-ago quarter; revenue rose 14 percent to $7.17 billion; firm hints at raising menu prices.
snippet: McDonald’s said that its third-quarter net income rose by 9 percent, but hinted that higher beef prices could cause it to raise menu prices again.
lead_paragraph: McDonald’s said that its third-quarter net income rose by 9 percent, but hinted that higher beef prices could cause it to raise menu prices again.

headline.main: Gains at McDonald’s Continue, but Menu Prices Could Rise
headline.print_headline: Gains at McDonald’s Continue, But Menu Prices Could Rise
headline.seo: McDonald’s Profit Is Up, but Prices May Follow
